# =============================================================================
# UASF frontend — environment template
# =============================================================================
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) for local overrides.
# On Vercel, set these as project-level environment variables.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API base URL
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The frontend supports two deployment models. Pick ONE:
#
#   MODE A — Same-origin via Vercel rewrite (recommended for Vercel).
#     Leave VITE_API_URL unset. The app will call `/api/*` which Vercel
#     rewrites to your backend per the `vercel.json` in the repo root.
#     You MUST edit `vercel.json` and replace BACKEND_PUBLIC_HOST_REPLACE_ME
#     with your backend's public host (e.g. `api.example.com`).
#
#   MODE B — Direct cross-origin to backend (simpler, but needs CORS).
#     Set VITE_API_URL to the fully-qualified backend API base. The backend
#     must allow the frontend's origin in FRONTEND_ORIGIN and must issue
#     `SameSite=None; Secure` cookies (COOKIE_SECURE=true on the backend).
#
# Example:
#   VITE_API_URL=https://api.uasf.example.com/api
#VITE_API_URL=
